dspace-development.title: Map the 2020 Senior Theses "East Asian Studies" certificate program Items into the DataSpace collection

comments.body:
The following correctly mapped the certificate program Items into the Collection in the staging environment:

```ruby
cert_handle = '88435/dsp016682x659t'
cert_collection = DSpace::CLI::SeniorThesisCollection.find_for_handle(cert_handle)
query = DSpace::CLI::SeniorThesisCommunity.find_by_class_year('2020')
cert_program = 'East Asian Studies Program'
sub_query = query.find_by_certificate_program(cert_program)
unmapped = sub_query.results.select { |i| i.collections.select { |c| c.title.include?(cert_program) }.empty? }
unmapped.map { |i| cert_collection.add_item(i); cert_collection.update }
cert_collection.index
```
These have been mapped and indexed into the production environment.

pulfalight.title: "View Content" should be renamed to "Download Content"

comments.body: What if the item is restricted from download and the user is only able to view? Are you suggesting this as a site wide change?

Not sure what you mean by buttons plural? I think it makes sense to leave the wording as is, or perhaps it could be changed to "access content"? I think the phrase needs to be both broad as well as instructional as there will be a few scenarios for how users will actually be able to access digital content based on restrictions, as Christa mentioned. "Download" seems to specific and potentially misleading. This may be something we want to check in with our colleagues about, including @sdellis and the Virtual RR group. Though, as far as I'm aware, no one has mentioned that the current wording is problematic or confusing. This scenario is similar to the Request button as several scenarios may apply in terms of whether something is restricted or needs review.

@ccleeton @faithc the time we think it's confusing is when there's a viewer right above it. What do you think about this scenario? Please see screenshots in the pull request for adding the viewer based on a query to figgy: https://github.com/pulibrary/pulfalight/pull/479

Ah, well to me then it makes sense to not even have a button in those cases. Is that possible--to know when content will be accessible via the viewer based on the link? I'm thinking no since restrictions are managed in Figgy?

pulfalight.title: Figure out Relative Links to PDFs for reading room

comments.body:
@tpendragon Are they in Figgy? If so, can you use the current method for logging in ("reading room functionality") to Figgy to display them to users? The general public can request to view these, so we would not be able to rely on PUID or CAS to authenticate users.

This is a policy question I think, so it might be a better question for Public Services.
I have not been part of any "virtual reading room" talks so I don't know what y'all have in mind for that, but @kelynch might have some insight on this too.
Assuming we want to mimic how this works on the current site? https://findingaids.princeton.edu/collections/C1491/c363. But agree this is a question for the virtual RR WG and Public Svs.
@faithc the current site limits viewership to people with Princeton IDs. My understanding is that the general public should be able to request to view. Do we have an option/path for this?
Think this is something @kelynch and the VRRWG have been reviewing.

Yes, we've started talking about implementing a request feature at some point, where the requests would go to a queue for Special Collections staff to review and potentially add for access.  I'll make sure this is on the agenda for the next VRR meeting.
